 It often occurs that an employee is required to work on Sundays owing to this either being the employee’s ordinary working day or due to a continuous shift pattern. Employers are then loath to pay anything in addition to the ordinary rate, as the employer feels that this is an ordinary working day. Section 16 of the Basic Conditions of Employment Act however provides differently: For any assistance in drafting contracts or assessing terms and conditions of employment, please do not hesitate to contact Goldberg & de Villiers, Tracey Mouton, Tel: (041) 501 9818, e-mail: traceym@goldlaw.co.za 